    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-02-07T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-02-07T19:00:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/2–751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation to the Torquay
                            Conference</gloss>, at Torquay, England</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d527fn1">Repeated to Paris for <gloss target="#t_OSR1"
                            >OSR</gloss> as 4128.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-02-07T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 7, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>356. Re <gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss>s 404, Feb 6 and 409, Feb 9
                        [7].<note n="2" xml:id="d527fn2">In Torquay telegram 409, February 7, 10
                        a.m., Phelps had asked urgently for some indication of “Washington
                        intentions” re: time extension of the conference and the extent of the
                        effort contemplated to prevent the breakdown, “possibly imminent,” of the
                        multilateral negotiations (394.31/2–751).</note>
                </p>
                <p>1. We believe US objectives in multilateral negots shld be (<hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi>) to achieve agreement on reductions at Torquay for inclusion in
                    Torquay <pb facs="1359" n="1343" xml:id="pg_1343"/> results, even if limited to
                    few items, and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) to obtain agreement on methods and
                    scope of similar negots to take place after Torquay. Not prepared to make more
                    detailed suggestions until UK motivations in resisting are better understood.
                    Hope firm decisions on scope negots can be deferred until Corse returns early
                    next week. However, if objective (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) gets in way of
                    achievement of (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>), our present inclination wld be to
                    concentrate on (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>), in order to give <gloss
                        target="#t_Benelux1">Benelux</gloss> some basis for signing Torquay
                    protocol.</p>
                <p>2. Prepared to make high level approach to appropriate govts if necessary to
                    avoid situation in which no real progress made at Torquay on either 1<hi
                        rend="italic">a</hi>) or 1(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>). Regard progress
                    through <gloss target="#t_MN1">MN</gloss>’s at Torquay important for continued
                    strength of <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> and critical for <gloss
                        target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> trade liberalization program.</p>
                <p>3. Time extension issue being handled separate tel.</p>
                <p>4. Personnel question in relation <gloss target="#t_MN1">MN</gloss>’s under
                    active consideration here. Decision soon.<note n="3" xml:id="d527fn3">This
                        refers to the Vernon assignment; see footnote 3, <ref target="#pg_1337">p.
                            1337</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>5. Above cleared with <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>, Interior, Labor.
                    Unable contact appropriate reps other agencies in time meet deadline.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
